edu.usc.scrc.PriorityPruner
Class SnpWorkUnit

java.lang.Object
  edu.usc.scrc.PriorityPruner.SnpWorkUnit

public class SnpWorkUnit
extends java.lang.Object

This class is used to find all the SNPs (in the given search range) that are in LD. The code for calculating LD is adapted from Haploview (Barrett et al.). Barrett JC, Fry B, Maller J, Daly MJ. Haploview: analysis and visualization of LD and haplotype maps. Bioinformatics. 2005 Jan 15 [PubMed ID: 15297300]

SnpWorkUnit

public SnpWorkUnit(java.lang.String snpName,
                   java.util.ArrayList<SnpGenotypes> genotypesList,
                   int referenceSNPIndex,
                   java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> founderIndices,
                   java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> subjectSexes,
                   double minMaf,
                   double minimumHardyWeinbergPvalue,
                   double minimumGenotypePercentage)
            throws PriorityPrunerException
Constructor for SnpWorkUnit. Initializes instance variables and initiates conversion of genotypes from compressed format to the original format used for LD calculation.

Parameters:
snpName - name of index SNP
genotypesList - list of SnpGenotypes-object within the current pruning window
referenceSNPIndex - the position of the index SNP in genotypesList
founderIndices - indices of founder subjects in the genotypes list. Right now we only support founders, so at the moment this corresponds to an index over all subjects chosen in this run
subjectSexes - the gender of subjects chosen in this run
minMaf - minimum allele frequency, as defined in command line
minimumHardyWeinbergPvalue - minimum Hardy-Weinberg p-value, as defined in command line
minimumGenotypePercentage - minimum genotype percentage, as defined in command line
Throws:
PriorityPrunerException - if problem are encountered during conversion (decompression) of genotypes
